Interface BiMap<K,V>

All Known Implementing Classes:
HashBiMap
public interface BiMap<K,V>
extends Map<K,V>

This interface allows for a bi-directional mapping, where keys can map to values and values can map to keys. This is expected to be used with one-to-oen mappings.

inverse

BiMap<V,K> inverse()
Returns a reversed form of this BiMap, where values in this BiMap will map to keys in this BiMap. Calling inverse on the returned BiMap should return a pointer to the original BiMap.
